12:07.925 --> 12:10.067
Will put
the Philly heat on them.

12:10.167 --> 12:11.789
Listen, that boy can play.

12:11.889 --> 12:13.390
Yeah,
I'm really proud of him.

12:13.490 --> 12:15.392
He'--he's amazing.

12:15.492 --> 12:17.474
Hold up.

12:22.579 --> 12:24.842
I wonder what that's about.

12:24.942 --> 12:27.685
Huh?
- I'll look into it.

12:27.785 --> 12:29.987
I'm out.

12:33.390 --> 12:34.531
Thanks for your help, Lisa.

12:34.631 --> 12:36.213
You let me know how
that test goes, OK?

12:36.313 --> 12:41.218
Will do.

12:41.318 --> 12:43.100
Hey.

12:43.200 --> 12:45.622
Hey, you're here early.

12:45.722 --> 12:47.865
Yeah, well, I knew
that you'd be tutoring,

12:47.965 --> 12:50.908
and I wanted to catch
you before class.

12:51.008 --> 12:53.030
For you.

12:55.893 --> 12:57.514
A swimmer charm?

12:57.614 --> 12:59.717
This is beautiful.

12:59.817 --> 13:01.478
But what's the occasion?

13:01.578 --> 13:04.401
Well, I'm still
in the Founder's Award race.

13:04.501 --> 13:09.006
Because what you said tapped
into what people want to hear.

13:09.106 --> 13:12.850
Well, and you're
always the one

13:12.950 --> 13:16.373
encouraging me
to speak my truth.

13:16.473 --> 13:19.737
And no matter who's against me,
you always have my back.

13:19.837 --> 13:21.378
I'll always be there for you.

13:21.478 --> 13:22.900
You know that.

13:23.000 --> 13:27.264
I just wanted to show you
how much I appreciate you, Lis.

13:27.364 --> 13:28.705
You mean the world to me,
and I don't know

13:28.805 --> 13:31.749
what I'd do without you.

13:31.849 --> 13:33.430
Thanks.

13:38.415 --> 13:40.277
All right,
I'll catch you later.

13:40.377 --> 13:41.959
Thanks.

13:50.387 --> 13:52.489
Yeah, that's good.
Thank you.

13:52.589 --> 13:56.774
Hey, look what I got,
vintage 1964.

13:56.874 --> 13:58.655
- Oh, come on now.
- Mm-hmm.

13:58.755 --> 14:00.257
Oh, I can hear Derek now.

14:00.357 --> 14:01.698
"Black folks
didn't get full rights

14:01.798 --> 14:03.260
under the law until 1964."

14:03.360 --> 14:04.701
"That's why
it's the only vintage

14:04.801 --> 14:06.583
we're gonna drink every year."

14:06.683 --> 14:08.946
That's right.

14:09.046 --> 14:11.188
I wish you were
still here, brother.

14:11.288 --> 14:14.191
Yeah, me too.

14:16.373 --> 14:18.395
You know,
about the Garrison account--

14:18.495 --> 14:19.596
No, no, no, no.

14:19.696 --> 14:22.599
Today is about memory
and celebration only.

14:22.699 --> 14:24.561
Today is about Derek.

14:24.661 --> 14:26.443
Right, right,
but you still think

14:26.543 --> 14:30.327
that this tribute
is a good idea

14:30.427 --> 14:32.129
given all the acquisition talk?

14:32.229 --> 14:33.770
Yeah, I mean, even more so.

14:33.870 --> 14:35.492
We've got to remind people
why me, you, and Derek

14:35.592 --> 14:37.254
started the firm
in the first place, right?

14:37.354 --> 14:39.016
I think they need
to hear from us.

14:39.116 --> 14:41.418
No, they need
to hear from you, Phil.

14:41.518 --> 14:43.901
And I need
to empty this bottle.

14:52.049 --> 14:55.152
Hey, Lis. Hold up.

14:55.252 --> 14:56.954
So how was class?

15:04.021 --> 15:07.124
Yo, C.

15:07.224 --> 15:09.126
Listen, man, we got to talk.

15:09.226 --> 15:10.687
We're doing that now, huh?

15:10.787 --> 15:14.611
No, no, no, but it's--
this is important.

15:14.711 --> 15:17.855
Look, Drew is the one who
leaked the locker room video.

15:17.955 --> 15:19.376
What?

15:19.476 --> 15:21.138
Yes, he basically admitted
it straight to my face.

15:21.238 --> 15:22.379
And the only reason
I'm telling you

15:22.479 --> 15:25.462
is because him and Lisa
are linked up right now.

15:25.562 --> 15:28.225
What--I thought
she was done with him.

15:28.325 --> 15:29.626
No, man, I guess
she gave him a second chance.

15:29.726 --> 15:30.747
I just saw them together.

15:30.847 --> 15:33.310
Look, man, you got
to tell her what's up.

15:33.410 --> 15:35.632
- Me?
- Yes.

15:35.732 --> 15:37.634
Me and Lisa, we're not
on good terms right now.

15:37.734 --> 15:39.276
You know?

15:39.376 --> 15:40.998
If I tell her, it will look
like I'm being a hater,

15:41.098 --> 15:43.840
but you guys are friends, OK?

15:43.940 --> 15:46.123
She's got to know what type
of guy she's fucking with.

15:46.223 --> 15:47.324
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

15:47.424 --> 15:49.686
Yeah, I'll talk to her.

15:49.786 --> 15:51.768
Good, see you later.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.411
Uh, hey, look, Will.

15:54.511 --> 15:58.575
For what it's worth, I'm sorry.

16:01.958 --> 16:04.021
That's not worth shit.

16:16.373 --> 16:20.717
To the Neeman Fellowship's
next executive director.

16:20.817 --> 16:23.760
OK, I have not accepted
the position yet.

16:23.860 --> 16:26.723
Oh, you could do whatever
you want with it now.

16:26.823 --> 16:29.806
I mean, you could carve out
some time for your own artwork

16:29.906 --> 16:31.808
and help new talent.

16:31.908 --> 16:34.451
<i>♪ No place
that I'd rather be ♪</i>

16:34.551 --> 16:36.173
Now, why aren't
you more excited?

16:36.273 --> 16:37.894
It's Janice.

16:37.994 --> 16:41.298
It's not like she's a friend,
but I feel like

16:41.398 --> 16:44.421
I'm stabbing a sister
in the back.

16:44.521 --> 16:46.944
OK, look,
I respect what Janice

16:47.044 --> 16:48.905
has done in the art world.

16:49.005 --> 16:50.627
But let's just be honest here.

16:50.727 --> 16:54.151
I mean, she should have
retired a long time ago.

16:54.251 --> 16:55.632
I mean, somebody's
going to get that job.

16:55.732 --> 16:56.994
Why not you?

16:57.094 --> 17:00.237
I just need to think
about it a bit more, I guess.

17:00.337 --> 17:01.838
OK, that's fair.

17:01.938 --> 17:04.601
I mean, let's just
not talk about Janice.

17:04.701 --> 17:07.884
Let's talk about the real
reason why I came over.

17:09.546 --> 17:13.730
Erika Baker is in LA.
So what's the plan?

17:13.830 --> 17:15.772
We gon' track that bitch down,
key her car,

17:15.872 --> 17:16.893
and slash her tires?

17:16.993 --> 17:18.255
OK, stop it.

17:18.355 --> 17:20.057
She still owes me
$20 in gas money.

17:20.157 --> 17:23.060
I have not forgotten.
- We're not in college anymore.

17:23.160 --> 17:25.662
And after what
she's done to you?

17:25.762 --> 17:27.344
That's just water
under the bridge?

17:29.526 --> 17:33.330
We are grown
and sophisticated women.

17:34.731 --> 17:36.073
Fine.

17:36.173 --> 17:37.874
I mean, you want
to take the high road.

17:37.974 --> 17:40.517
I mean, it's boring, but OK.

17:40.617 --> 17:43.200
Look, she and Phil have
a professional connection now.

17:43.300 --> 17:47.004
And I'm trying to give him
the space to just work it out.

17:47.104 --> 17:49.246
Hmm.

17:49.346 --> 17:51.928
What I see is,
you are trying to be

17:52.028 --> 17:57.574
considerate of everyone else,
I mean, Janice, Erika, Phil.

17:57.674 --> 17:59.416
And while you're
so busy putting

17:59.516 --> 18:03.940
everyone else's feelings first,
who's dealing with yours?

18:04.040 --> 18:06.103
Hmm?

18:09.366 --> 18:12.149
For your project,
each team will build

18:12.249 --> 18:16.113
a functional robot capable
of completing three tasks.

18:16.213 --> 18:18.115
You all can pick
whatever tasks those are.

18:18.215 --> 18:20.277
The teams will be as follows:

18:20.377 --> 18:24.321
Madison and Sophia,
Luke and Kaya,

18:24.421 --> 18:26.883
Ashley and Olivia...

18:29.065 --> 18:31.328
Mason and Justin,

18:31.428 --> 18:34.331
Akasha and Laila,
Jim and Fred.

18:34.431 --> 18:36.493
<i>♪ Trying to see
if she like me ♪</i>

18:36.593 --> 18:39.896
<i>♪ Maybe she could be
my wifey ♪</i>

18:39.996 --> 18:43.220
Damn, I love your spot.

18:43.320 --> 18:44.821
It's not put together yet.

18:44.921 --> 18:47.504
Just moved in a week ago;
all I need is some furniture

18:47.604 --> 18:50.947
and a woman's touch.

18:51.047 --> 18:52.989
I remember your first place
in Santa Monica,

18:53.089 --> 18:54.351
the townhouse.

18:54.451 --> 18:56.633
I bought it
with my rookie signing bonus.

18:56.733 --> 18:59.356
Mm-hmm, and you could
not stop smiling.

18:59.456 --> 19:01.037
Kind of like now.

19:03.540 --> 19:05.722
- Are you fucking kidding me?
- You up for a dip?

19:05.822 --> 19:08.405
I know your ass still
look good in a bikini.

19:08.505 --> 19:10.847
I'm here for business.

19:10.947 --> 19:12.369
All right, cool.

19:12.469 --> 19:14.631
We could start with that.

19:16.673 --> 19:19.576
OK, so I'm looking to get
more engagement for the house.

19:19.676 --> 19:21.698
And I have some football
cross-promotion ideas.

19:21.798 --> 19:23.460
I would love to talk
to you about them.

19:23.560 --> 19:25.742
Look at you being a boss.

19:25.842 --> 19:28.865
Well, it's no billboard
on Sunset, but I'm trying.

19:28.965 --> 19:30.267
Billboard?

19:30.367 --> 19:31.748
Yeah,
my business partner, Ivy,

19:31.848 --> 19:33.710
she has product lines
and merch.

19:33.810 --> 19:35.312
And she's always bragging
that they're gonna

19:35.412 --> 19:36.753
give her some billboard
on Sunset

19:36.853 --> 19:39.916
for her nasty-ass water, H2Ivy.

19:40.016 --> 19:42.239
Gotcha, OK.

19:42.339 --> 19:44.441
So how can I help?

19:44.541 --> 19:46.723
So I created
a business strategy.

19:46.823 --> 19:49.406
If you like it,
maybe you can connect me

19:49.506 --> 19:52.249
with your marketing people?

19:52.349 --> 19:53.650
Done.

19:53.750 --> 19:55.572
Wait, don't you want
to look at it first?

19:55.672 --> 20:00.457
They're your ideas, so I
already know it's brilliant.

20:00.557 --> 20:03.540
Yo, Gerry, it's LaMarcus Alton.

20:03.640 --> 20:05.822
Hey, you got a minute?

20:08.845 --> 20:12.909
When James, Derek, and I
decided to start this firm,

20:13.009 --> 20:16.913
we made a pact that we would
watch out for each other

20:17.013 --> 20:20.357
and that we were gonna
change the world.

20:20.457 --> 20:24.040
We made a promise that we were
gonna kick down those doors

20:24.140 --> 20:25.442
that were closed to us,

20:25.542 --> 20:28.925
so that the next generation
wouldn't have to.

20:29.025 --> 20:33.129
Not everyone wanted to see
three brothers succeed.

20:35.472 --> 20:37.093
We alternated paying
our mortgages

20:37.193 --> 20:38.295
just to keep this place afloat.

20:38.395 --> 20:39.776
Mm-hmm.

20:39.876 --> 20:42.819
So when we lost Derek
to a massive heart attack,

20:42.919 --> 20:44.741
we thought that might
be the end of the firm.

20:44.841 --> 20:47.824
But we fought harder, because
we know that our brother

20:47.924 --> 20:49.786
would have wanted us
to run this race,

20:49.886 --> 20:51.908
even though he couldn't
be here to cross

20:52.008 --> 20:53.310
the finish line with us.

20:53.410 --> 20:55.432
Which is why we gather here
every year in his name,

20:55.532 --> 20:57.594
to recognise
the day of his passing

20:57.694 --> 21:02.719
and pay tribute to how far
we've all come together.

21:02.819 --> 21:04.321
To Derek.
- To Derek.

21:04.421 --> 21:06.323
all: To Derek.

21:38.134 --> 21:38.995
I'll catch you later.

21:39.095 --> 21:41.598
See ya.

21:41.698 --> 21:44.060
Were you ever gonna
tell me about you and Drew?

21:47.023 --> 21:48.485
People change.

21:48.585 --> 21:50.206
You should know that
better than anyone.

21:50.306 --> 21:53.009
- He's not who you think he is.
- What's that supposed to mean?

21:53.109 --> 21:54.931
He's the one that airdropped
the locker room video of me.

21:55.031 --> 21:56.693
What?
That's ridiculous.

21:56.793 --> 21:57.534
Is it?

21:57.634 --> 21:59.175
Ever since I came to the BSU,

21:59.275 --> 22:01.258
the dude's been trying
to ruin my fucking life.

22:01.358 --> 22:02.619
Carlton, stop.

22:02.719 --> 22:04.140
Why are you defending him?

22:04.240 --> 22:07.864
Because I think
I know what this is about.

22:07.964 --> 22:10.146
If I led you to believe
that we were anything

22:10.246 --> 22:12.589
more than friends, I'm sorry.

22:12.689 --> 22:16.853
But that is all
that we will ever be.

22:19.295 --> 22:23.059
No, I'm sorry.

22:23.860 --> 22:25.882
I'm sorry you're so desperate
to get over Will

22:25.982 --> 22:27.524
that you're willing
to jump the first asshole

22:27.624 --> 22:29.406
that pays you any attention.

22:34.070 --> 22:35.652
Fuck you.

22:37.834 --> 22:42.138
<i>♪ As I lay in this
four-wall hotel ♪</i>

22:45.562 --> 22:48.385
<i>♪ I wonder if you think
of me ♪</i>

22:53.009 --> 22:56.513
<i>♪ All I've got left
is my bottle of gin ♪</i>

22:56.613 --> 23:00.156
<i>♪ My bottle of gin ♪</i>

23:00.256 --> 23:05.602
<i>♪ Your words still haunt
my aching soul ♪</i>

23:07.624 --> 23:11.167
<i>♪ You might win the fight,
but you lost the war ♪</i>

23:11.267 --> 23:15.011
<i>♪ You lost someone, you lost,
you lost ♪</i>

23:15.111 --> 23:17.334
<i>♪ You lost someone,
you lost the war ♪</i>

23:17.434 --> 23:20.136
What's up?

23:20.236 --> 23:22.619
Do you have any
more peace offerings?

23:23.880 --> 23:26.543
What happened to,
"Fuck off, Connor"?

23:26.643 --> 23:29.466
What can I say?
You know me.

23:29.566 --> 23:33.350
I knew you could use it.

23:33.450 --> 23:35.852
I could use a little more.

23:39.776 --> 23:41.718
All right, follow me.

23:57.994 --> 24:01.378
Come on.

24:01.478 --> 24:04.320
Let's go.

24:05.682 --> 24:08.585
Hey, you need some help?

24:08.685 --> 24:09.906
No, thanks.

24:10.006 --> 24:11.307
Are you sure?

24:11.407 --> 24:13.149
I've been driving
my dad's car.

24:13.249 --> 24:15.872
I don't--he was
supposed to take it

24:15.972 --> 24:17.394
in the shop, and he didn't.

24:17.494 --> 24:18.595
And now I'm stuck.

24:18.695 --> 24:20.717
Well, I could, uh...

24:20.817 --> 24:22.078
give you a ride home
if you want.

24:22.178 --> 24:23.720
I'm not going home.

24:23.820 --> 24:25.882
I'm going to the hospital.

24:25.982 --> 24:27.323
Angela's in labor.

24:27.423 --> 24:30.006
- Shit, like right now?
- Yes.

24:30.106 --> 24:31.167
Well, come on.
I can give you a ride.

24:31.267 --> 24:32.368
I'm good.

24:32.468 --> 24:33.570
Lisa, I'm not just
gonna let you sit here.

24:33.670 --> 24:35.672
I said I'm fine, Will.

24:38.915 --> 24:41.798
OK.

24:43.640 --> 24:45.502
I'm fine. I'm fine.

25:03.059 --> 25:04.240
You're late.

25:04.340 --> 25:06.763
I wasn't even sure
you'd show.

25:06.863 --> 25:10.406
I think we should make
a robot that sorts recyclables.

25:10.506 --> 25:14.771
I was thinking a cleaning
robot that sweeps floors.

25:14.871 --> 25:18.114
Let's just see
what parts we have.

25:21.037 --> 25:24.300
So have you talked to her?

25:24.400 --> 25:25.421
Who?

25:25.521 --> 25:27.383
Mrs. Hughes.

25:27.483 --> 25:28.785
Why do you care?

25:28.885 --> 25:31.868
She was
my favourite teacher too.

25:31.968 --> 25:33.950
Then why'd you snitch on her?

25:34.050 --> 25:36.072
I would never do that.

25:36.172 --> 25:40.156
It wasn't me.
- It wasn't?

25:40.256 --> 25:42.438
I used to be her favourite,

25:42.538 --> 25:45.762
so I was a little jealous that
she was giving you attention.

25:45.862 --> 25:47.363
That's all.

25:47.463 --> 25:49.846
Oh, my bad.

25:49.946 --> 25:51.888
I shouldn't have jumped
to conclusions.

25:51.988 --> 25:53.930
I guess that makes two of us.

25:54.030 --> 25:57.053
I thought you were
a stuck-up mean girl.

25:57.153 --> 25:59.776
That's not me at all.

25:59.876 --> 26:02.258
I'm just kind of shy.

26:02.358 --> 26:05.441
I get that.
I am too.

26:08.524 --> 26:10.907
The cleaning robot
seems good.

26:11.007 --> 26:12.829
Maybe it will clean my room
for me.

26:12.929 --> 26:14.711
Yeah.

26:24.260 --> 26:26.963
So these are
your new friends now?

26:27.063 --> 26:28.244
You jealous?

26:28.344 --> 26:30.166
We met at a girl's pool party.

26:30.266 --> 26:31.968
We hang out every now and then.

26:32.068 --> 26:33.129
Yo, I left
all my shit in the car,

26:33.229 --> 26:34.290
so let's just get in
and get out.

26:34.390 --> 26:37.534
OK, they said,
"Come on in now."

26:43.720 --> 26:46.743
<i>♪ They want the sound,
want the sound ♪</i>

26:48.885 --> 26:50.627
Yo!

26:50.727 --> 26:52.228
What's up?

26:52.328 --> 26:54.230
<i>♪ Green beret,
used to be on the benches ♪</i>

26:54.330 --> 26:57.073
<i>♪ Now with cigars
and creme brulée ♪</i>

26:57.173 --> 27:00.957
Gentlemen and gentlemen,
pick your pleasure,

27:01.057 --> 27:05.882
snorted, injected, or smoked.

27:05.982 --> 27:07.403
Let's party.

27:07.503 --> 27:08.885
Actually,
we weren't gonna stay.

27:08.985 --> 27:11.728
We were--
- Well, I mean, why not?

27:11.828 --> 27:13.690
- Yeah.
- Why not?

27:13.790 --> 27:16.853
<i>♪ So line 'em up,
line 'em up, line 'em up ♪</i>

27:18.514 --> 27:20.336
You were right.

27:20.436 --> 27:22.018
I'm glad we did this today.

27:22.118 --> 27:24.100
It felt good.

27:24.200 --> 27:28.544
Well, as usual,
everyone responds to you.

27:28.644 --> 27:32.148
I hope we made
our brother Derek proud.

27:32.248 --> 27:33.590
I'm sure he would
have had a lot to say

27:33.690 --> 27:37.994
about that fake-ass tribute.

27:38.094 --> 27:40.156
I just got
an interesting call.

27:40.256 --> 27:42.879
You know, our law world
is small, Phil.

27:42.979 --> 27:46.002
And the Black one's
even smaller.

27:46.102 --> 27:49.085
What, did you think
I wasn't gonna find out?

27:49.185 --> 27:51.487
My meeting
with Carson & Lake.

27:51.587 --> 27:53.409
Yeah, you called me out
about having a secret meeting.

27:53.509 --> 27:56.132
And it seems like you've
been having some of your own.

27:56.232 --> 27:58.735
It's an old friend,
Erika Baker.

27:58.835 --> 28:00.897
She's a partner there.

28:00.997 --> 28:03.099
Damn, Phil.

28:03.199 --> 28:04.260
I mean, brother,
you're a big part

28:04.360 --> 28:05.702
of why we're in this position.

28:05.802 --> 28:07.263
Now you're just going to bail
and look out for yourself?

28:07.363 --> 28:08.384
She asked me to come in.
All right?

28:08.484 --> 28:09.786
It was just an introduction
to the team.

28:09.886 --> 28:12.508
OK, so, you're not
considering a real offer?

28:20.136 --> 28:21.958
Well, congratulations.

28:22.058 --> 28:24.120
You just fooled everyone
into thinking

28:24.220 --> 28:26.562
that you still care
about this place.

28:38.274 --> 28:40.056
You didn't
have to come inside.

28:40.156 --> 28:41.337
Yeah, well,
it didn't seem like you

28:41.437 --> 28:43.760
wanted to walk in alone, so...

28:46.042 --> 28:48.304
A baby brother.

28:48.404 --> 28:49.946
That's cool, right?

28:50.046 --> 28:52.548
I don't know.

28:52.648 --> 28:54.811
It's weird.

28:56.372 --> 29:01.758
My dad's rebuilt a new life,
a new wife, a new baby.

29:01.858 --> 29:07.043
It's like I'm on the outside

29:07.143 --> 29:12.268
watching a whole other family
spring up that isn't mine.

29:18.674 --> 29:20.676
Um...

29:23.759 --> 29:25.581
You know what?

29:25.681 --> 29:27.683
It's cool.

29:29.125 --> 29:31.407
I can hang.

29:34.690 --> 29:37.573
Come in.

29:41.017 --> 29:44.320
Viv, wow, what a surprise.

29:44.420 --> 29:46.202
God, it's--
it's been forever.

29:46.302 --> 29:47.884
Wow, you look fantastic.

29:47.984 --> 29:51.107
